post_text: South Tama Activity Boosters, Inc. recently began its 2020 Membership Drive. Citizens of Tama, Toledo, Chelsea, and Montour received a membership form in the mail. Please look for the blue card stock form! South Tama Activity Boosters, Inc. supports all student activities within the South Tama County School District. These activities include fine arts, music, band, athletics, academics, cheer, and clubs including the South Tama Archery Club and Gamer’s Club. The organization has purchased training equipment, funded major facility projects, and purchased items to support programs. South Tama Activity Boosters, Inc. sponsors several annual events: Kolpin Open Golf Fundraiser, Jam the Gym, and Pin the Gym. Please consider becoming a member of this important organization! #thetrojanway

Looking for people with chainsaws that are willing to go around with the team and cut up trees while the players move trees and debris....community we are going to divide and conquer walking around neighborhoods looking to help, so feel free to let us know where to go or if you see us walking by don't hesitate to stop and ask for help....we are in this together....Go Trojans!

shared_text:
STC Cheerleading
March 8 at 7:02 PM ·

STC Cheer will be hosting tryouts Friday, March 20, 2020. We are a program that focuses on school spirit, promoting school pride and supporting athletic teams.

STC Cheer has 28 spots we would like to fill for the 2020-21 school year. In the next two weeks we will be sharing some videos of STC Cheer alumni talking about the positive impact that cheer had in their lives.

Come see what our program is about. We are hosting Cheer Clinics Wednesday, March 11 from 3:45 to 4:45; Wednesday, March 18 from 2:45 to 3:45; and Thursday, March 19 from 3:45 to 4:45 at the elementary gym.

shared_text:
STC Cheerleading
March 1 at 9:41 PM ·

STC Cheer is offering Cheer Clinics during the month of March! We are looking for energetic individuals to be a part of our Cheer Squads. All students entering grades 9th-12th during the 2020-21 school year are invited to attend. Each week we will work on cheers, chants and jumps as well as some cheer routines. If you have considered cheer, but are not quite sure, this is the time to find out! Come to one or all of them! If you have any questions, please contact Coach Chris Drummer (cdrummer@s-tama.k12.ia.us) or Allison Graham (agraham@s-tama.k12.ia.us)

Clinic dates and times are:
Wednesday, March 4th 2:45-4:00
Wednesday, March 11th 3:45-5:00
Wednesday, March 18th 2:45-4:00
Thursday, March 19th 3:45-5:00

2020-21 Cheer Tryouts
Friday, March 20th 4:30-6:30

Update from 2020 IHSAA State Wrestling Championships:
2A-126
Sophomore Logan Arp
Rnd 1: lost 2-5 to E. DeLeon (Bishop Heelan)
Cons.Rnd1: won 7-1 vs EWoods (W Delaware)
Cons.Rnd2: won 10-6 vs SNelson (Clear Lake)
Cons.Rnd3: won by fall vs TKiedam (SBLuton)
Arp will wrestle for third place Saturday Morning.

Cons.Rnd3: won by fall vs JNeuhaus (WDelaware)
Vest will wrestle for third place Saturday Morning.

2A-170
Junior Brayden Smith
Rnd 1: lost by fall to JVoss (W Delaware)
Cons.Rnd1: lost by fall vs CBendorf (Harlan)
Congratulations on a great season, Brayden!

Mike Carnahan
February 9 at 5:19 PM ·

Wow! Just had an amazing rehearsal for our jazz band with guest clinician Kevin Brown! He judged us at State a couple weeks ago and was very enthusiastic to work with us in the future. We were happy we made it work in short order and the knowledge he gave us will be invaluable as we continue to improve for NEIBA Jazz Festival on March 7. Thank you to the students as well who made a rehearsal on a weekend work, not required to be there, but dedicated to improving!
text:
Mike Carnahan
February 9 at 5:19 PM ·

Wow! Just had an amazing rehearsal for our jazz band with guest clinician Kevin Brown! He judged us at State a couple weeks ago and was very enthusiastic to work with us in the future. We were happy we made it work in short order and the knowledge he gave us will be invaluable as we continue to improve for NEIBA Jazz Festival on March 7. Thank you to the students as well who made a rehearsal on a weekend work, not required to be there, but dedicated to improving!

February 7 at 3:28 PM ·

Iowa Girls High School Athletic Union releases regional pairings

http://tamatoledonews.com/page/content.detail/id/610218/Iowa-Girls-High-School-Athletic-Union-releases-regional-pairings.html?nav=5011

post_text: Freshmen Katie Husak and Joseph Withrow are participating in the ISU Cyclone Honor Band this weekend, both in the “Gold Band” which is made up of select All-Staters. This is a band of some of the best of the best high school musicians in the state! Their director for this event is Dr. Leslie Hicken, Professor Emeritus from Furman University in Greenville, South Carolina. They will rehearse all day, ending around 9:00 pm, and rehearse most of the day tomorrow before putting on a public performance at CY Stephens Auditorium on the ISU campus at 3:00. Way to represent STC Katie and Joseph!

shared_text:
Toledo-Tama Kiwanis Club
February 5 at 10:13 PM ·

February 5, 2020: Wow! Today Kiwanis members had the privilege of meeting and listening to the music of STC student, Katie Husak. Already this year Katie's musical talents have earned her a place in the ISU Cyclone Honor Band-Gold Band, the UNI Northern Festival Honor Band-Wind Symphony, NEIBA Honor Band, WAMAC Conference Honor Band, and All State Honor Band! All these honors and Katie is only a FRESHMAN!! STC Band Director Mike Carnahan introduced Katie and the two of them spoke to the amount of training, practice and work that goes into preparation for these band trials and performances. Many thanks to Katie and Mike for taking time out of their school day to be with Kiwanis today. Also pictured is Kiwanis member Cindy Roth, February's program organizer.

post_text: IAHSAA has released the new football districts. South Tama will compete in Class 2A District 6 with Mount Vernon, Solon, Union, Center Point Urbana, and Vinton-Shellsburg. Go Big Blue! #thetrojanway
